<div>		



<span class="section_title">SBC Communications CEO Edward Whitacre, Jr. To Deliver Industry Insider Address at The 2005 International CES</span>

	<br><br>
	<span class="subhead">Whitacre Joins Judy McGrath of MTV Networks and Mike Ramsay of TiVo </span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/23/2004</i></strong>
<br><br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today announced that SBC Communications Inc. chairman and CEO Edward E. Whitacre Jr., will deliver an Industry Insider address at the 2005 International CES on Thursday, January, 6 at 10:30 a.m., in room N250 of the Las Vegas Convention Center (LVCC).  The 2005 International CES, the world's largest annual technology showcase, will be held in Las Vegas, Nev. from January 6-9.  
<p>
"Ed Whitacre's vision has helped SBC Communications become a remarkable leader in the growth of the telecommunications industry, particularly in regard to wireless communications and high-speed DSL service," said Gary Shapiro, CEA president and CEO, the producer of the International CES.  "We are excited to have Ed as a first time Industry Insider at the International CES to offer his thoughts on the convergence of consumer entertainment and communications technologies and how it will impact the digital revolution."  
<p>
SBC Communications Inc. recently announced separate agreements with Microsoft and Yahoo! That will create new opportunities to integrate communications and entertainment services across home video and audio systems, PCs, mobile devices and other network-enabled equipment.  Using the capabilities of its advanced broadband networks, SBC companies plan to evolve "The Digital Home" to "The Digital Lifestyle." 
<p>
Under Whitacre's leadership, the SBC family of companies has grown from a regional telephone company into one of the world's most successful and innovative communications and entertainment providers.  SBC subsidiaries own a majority share of Cingular Wireless(, the nation's largest wireless provider, lead the nation in high-speed DSL lines and offer satellite TV service branded as SBC ( DISH Network.  Whitacre was made president and chief operating officer in October 1988. In that position, he was responsible for the operation of SBC's six primary subsidiaries. On January 1, 1990, Whitacre assumed his current position as SBC's chairman of the board and chief executive officer. 
<p>
Earlier this year, SBC Communications Inc. was named by Fortune as America's Most Admired Telecommunications Company for the fifth consecutive year and eighth time in nine years.  The company also received the honor of being named World's Most Admired Telecommunications Company for the seventh year in a row.
<p>
Whitacre joins Judy McGrath, chairman and CEO, MTV Networks and Mike Ramsay, co-founder, chairman and CEO of TiVo Inc., as confirmed Industry Insiders for the 2005 International CES.  McGrath's address will take place on Thursday, January 6, at 2:30 p.m. in room N250 of the LVCC.  Ramsay's address will take place on Friday, January 7, at 10:30 a.m. in room N250.  
<p>

Note to Journalists:  	Detailed CES press information, including press room hours and services, press events and registration, is available at www.CESweb.org/press.  Journalists are encouraged to arrive in Las Vegas by Tuesday, January 4, 2005 to take advantage of all the CES press conferences and events.  CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES will run January 4 from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. in the Las Vegas Convention Center, room S226, across the hallway from the CES Press Room.  
<p>

About CEA: <br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 1,750 corporate members involved in the design, development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, information technology, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $90 billion in annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at www.CE.org, the definitive source for information about the consumer electronics industry. <br>
CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.


